<http://www.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/event/43601AMKQJGTDVBKLNSTTJVLMKDNDDDLS>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Task It! Space Object Improv with Mary Saunders";
  schema:description """
	<h2>Date: Saturday May 2</h2><h2>Time: 3:30pm-5:30pm </h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Ages 19+</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">$75</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Level Required:</span> Improv 102 or equivalent experience (email education@theimprovcentre.ca if you’re not sure).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In this workshop we’ll be exploring the significance of tasking in our scenes and how it can be used to communicate beyond our words. We’ll discuss and practice basic technique, commitment, and ultimately how this comes together to diversify the visual and emotional landscape of our scenes beyond dialogue alone.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>About the teacher:<span><br/></span>Mary (she/they) is a Vancouver-based comedian. Her initial improv training was with Instant Theatre and UBCimprov, then later Blind Tiger Comedy. Now she can be regularly found performing as a Mainstage ensemble member at The Improv Centre, a co-creator and producer of WikiProv, and a member of Grad School Improv. Mary is passionate about using her over 10 years experience as a foundation for teaching others the skills they need to begin and expand their own improv journeys. Mary is also a satirist, having published works via Reductress and the Beaverton, and a sketch comedian. Mary is stoked to be here and would do anything for you.<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Workshop Capacity: 14 people
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-05-02T15:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/files/e75bf5b7-80d5-4ead-be88-8f45ca46ac85.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/location/603AMBLCJQMLRJDMDQKBNHDKQPPDPCQLJ>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/organization/the-improv-centre>;
  schema:url <https://theimprovcentre.ca/shows/>;
  schema:offers _:002da49907ad4172abad71415d1299175445;
  schema:duration "PT60M";
  schema:endDate "2026-05-02T16:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

